Subject: CK: add FMHA receipt 700 (TransformerEngine integration)

Mirror of ROCm/rocm-libraries#6867 ("Added custom FMHA codegen receipt
for TransformerEngine"), rebased onto AITER's vendored CK layout
(3rdparty/composable_kernel/...). Adds a TE-specific receipt that
generates a much smaller kernel set than receipt 600:

  - fwd:  fp16/bf16 only, row vlayout, has_lse, no skip/sink/logits/qscale
  - bwd:  fp16/bf16 only, dropout in {no, dropout_wg32, dropout_wg16}
  - splitkv / batch_prefill / pagedkv_prefill: skipped (TE does not use)

To actually exercise this receipt, switch the libmha_fwd / libmha_bwd
blob_gen_cmd entries from `--receipt 600` to `--receipt 700`. Until
that switch lands, this patch only adds the receipt; it does not
change any generated output.

Upstream PR: https://github.com/ROCm/rocm-libraries/pull/6867

diff --git a/3rdparty/composable_kernel/example/ck_tile/01_fmha/codegen/ops/fmha_batch_prefill.py b/3rdparty/composable_kernel/example/ck_tile/01_fmha/codegen/ops/fmha_batch_prefill.py
--- a/3rdparty/composable_kernel/example/ck_tile/01_fmha/codegen/ops/fmha_batch_prefill.py
+++ b/3rdparty/composable_kernel/example/ck_tile/01_fmha/codegen/ops/fmha_batch_prefill.py
@@ -878,6 +878,8 @@ def get_fwd_blobs(
                         cond &= pipeline.F_qscale == "no"
                         if not cond:
                             continue
+                    elif receipt == 700:
+                        continue  # TE does not use this API

                     # fp32 only
                     if receipt == 800 or receipt == 801:
diff --git a/3rdparty/composable_kernel/example/ck_tile/01_fmha/codegen/ops/fmha_bwd.py b/3rdparty/composable_kernel/example/ck_tile/01_fmha/codegen/ops/fmha_bwd.py
